parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can lead to serious injury or death in the event of a crash, as airbags may not deploy or may deploy incorrectly.
symptoms: The airbag light is on or flashing
the airbag system is not functioning properly
the airbag does not deploy in a crash

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag sensors can cause the airbags to malfunction or not deploy in a crash, leading to serious injury or death.
symptoms: The airbag light is on or flashing
the airbag system is not functioning properly
the airbag does not deploy in a crash.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: An electrical short in the airbag module can cause the airbag system to malfunction or not deploy in a crash, leading to serious injury or death.
symptoms: The airbag light is on or flashing
the airbag system is not functioning properly
the airbag does not deploy in a crash.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive engine oil consumption can lead to premature engine wear, increased emissions, and potentially cause engine failure, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Engine consumes one quart of oil every 1000 miles

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A stuck throttle can cause the vehicle to accelerate uncontrollably, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: Throttle sticks at full or nearly full acceleration

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause the vehicle to lose power or stall, leading to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
Sudden stalling can cause accidents or leave the driver stranded.
Failure of the evaporative emission system can cause the vehicle to emit excessive pollutants, contributing to environmental harm.
Electrical system failure can cause the vehicle to catch fire, leading to accidents or injuries.
Unwanted ABS activation can cause the vehicle to lose traction, leading to loss of control, accidents, or near-miss incidents.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Failure/Faltering at Slow Stopping Speeds
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake failure or faltering at slow stopping speeds can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities due to the inability to stop the vehicle in a timely manner.
symptoms: Brakes fail or falter when applied at slow stopping speeds

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Defective brake pads and rotors can cause the brakes to malfunction, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
